rate (PER) percentage of both QCNN and CNN based models 
on the TIMIT phoneme recognition task. The results are from 
a 3 folds average. 'L' stands for number of Layers, 'FM' for 
number of feature maps, and 'Params' for number of learning 
parameters. The latter is expressed in order to be equivalent 
for both models. Therefore, 32FM is equal to 32FM for real
